Creophilus erythrocephalus var. oculatus
;
Lea, 1925: 229
(synonym of
C. erythrocephalus
).

subSubSection.paragraph:
Diagnosis:
With characters of the 

erythrocephalus

- group; temporal regions and postgena orange-red, rest of integument and elytra uniformly pitchy-black (
Fig. 1C
); apex of antennomere 11 produced into distinct ridge (
Fig. 32B
); macropterous (
Fig. 33N
); last protarsomere much longer than preceding two together (
Fig. 33J
); elytral discal series with three or four macrosetae; tergal chaetotaxic formula = 4-6-6-6- 4-6.
